I"—<p>The Bitter Lesson argues that, based on empirical observations of the field, machine learning should focus on developing <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/deep-learning-is-consonant-with-empiricism">meta-level learning strategies</a>, based on which the model would derive the rest, compared to engineering <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/deep-learning-is-consonant-with-empiricism">symbolic domain-specific knowledge</a> into the system. In a similar manner, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/predestined-learning-breaks-nature-nurture-dichotomy">predestined learning helps people derive rich, but similar, worldviews</a>.</p>
